hopobject.body: My battery's about to run out imigran costa rica Ruffelle is hoping that the show will “have a life” and transfer to New York, as her previous show, the autobiographical Beneath the Dress, did. But most of all, she hopes that Paris Original will let her fans in on a different side to her. “It’s taken me a long time but I feel as if I’m growing up. It will be nice for the fans who know me and my voice from Les Mis to see, however many years later, the person I’ve turned into.”
